  "prompt": "What does \u597d\u840c\u963f mean?",
  "response": "\"\u597d\u840c\u963f\" (h\u01ceo m\u00e9ng a) is a phrase in Chinese that translates to \"so cute\" or \"really cute\" in English. The term \"\u840c\" (m\u00e9ng) specifically refers to something that is cute or adorable, often used in the context of animals, characters, or anything that elicits a sense of cuteness. The \"\u597d\" (h\u01ceo) means \"very\" or \"so,\" and \"\u963f\" (a) is a particle that adds an informal or affectionate tone to the expression. Overall, it's a casual and positive way to express admiration for something that is perceived as cute.",
